Carter?

89
00:07:04.980 --> 00:07:05.858
Carter.

90
00:07:05.858 --> 00:07:06.837
He's not breathing.

91
00:07:06.838 --> 00:07:08.850
Carter? Carter. can you hear me?

92
00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:16.949
We had a... a deal.

93
00:07:16.950 --> 00:07:18.963
I help you. and you-you do what?

94
00:07:18.964 --> 00:07:20.987
You stay way away from me.

95
00:07:20.988 --> 00:07:22.907
- Forever.
- And that was my every intention. Ritchie.

96
00:07:22.908 --> 00:07:27.443
No magic. no demons. no John
Constantine whatso-damn-ever.

97
00:07:27.444 --> 00:07:28.803
You swore it.

98
00:07:28.804 --> 00:07:29.712
You promised me.

99
00:07:29.713 --> 00:07:31.280
Gary's dead. Ritchie.

100
00:07:34.660 --> 00:07:37.106
W...

101
00:07:37.130 --> 00:07:39.670
Wait.

102
00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:43.296
D... dead?

103
00:07:43.320 --> 00:07:46.186
I'm sorry to spring it
on you like that. mate.

104
00:07:46.210 --> 00:07:48.236
but. uh. now I have it on good authority

105
00:07:48.260 --> 00:07:49.906
that something ill-natured is circling you

106
00:07:49.930 --> 00:07:51.686
like a pack of wolves.

107
00:07:51.710 --> 00:07:54.250
and I'm not just gonna sit
there and wait for it to attack.

108
00:07:56.216 --> 00:07:58.986
Why me? I...

109
00:07:59.010 --> 00:08:00.556
Have you noticed... I-I teach class.

110
00:08:00.580 --> 00:08:02.578
I hold office hours. and I go home.

111
00:08:02.579 --> 00:08:06.701
And I partake of a whole
lot of sedatives in between.

112
00:08:07.260 --> 00:08:08.630
And that's all I do.

113
00:08:09.030 --> 00:08:10.484
What about the data-mining?

114
00:08:11.260 --> 00:08:12.749
You found any unusual spikes

115
00:08:12.750 --> 00:08:14.163
in activity around the campus here?

116
00:08:14.164 --> 00:08:15.933
The data-mining.

117
00:08:15.934 --> 00:08:17.655
You know what?

118
00:08:17.656 --> 00:08:20.902
You gaze at the chaos long enough...

119
00:08:20.903 --> 00:08:23.920
can swallow you whole.

120
00:08:23.943 --> 00:08:26.315
I shut my program down.

121
00:08:26.338 --> 00:08:27.670
You shut it down?

122
00:08:27.675 --> 00:08:29.335
That's right.

123
00:08:29.336 --> 00:08:31.321
You know what I'm focusing on now?

124
00:08:31.322 --> 00:08:32.351
Solutions.

125
00:08:32.352 --> 00:08:34.290
What exactly are those solutions. Ritchie?

126
00:08:34.291 --> 00:08:36.709
Oh. would you like to hear
some...? Here's the first one.

127
00:08:37.628 --> 00:08:39.025
Solutions.

128
00:08:40.174 --> 00:08:41.799
Yes. Adam.

129
00:08:41.800 --> 00:08:43.317
Professor Simpson.

130
00:08:44.420 --> 00:08:46.573
I need to talk to you about
my office hours today.

131
00:08:46.574 --> 00:08:47.975
My friend Carter.

132
00:08:47.976 --> 00:08:50.060
he. uh...

133
00:08:50.061 --> 00:08:52.526
he collapsed outside of his dorm.

134
00:08:52.527 --> 00:08:55.459
He's dead.

135
00:08:55.460 --> 00:08:57.886
I...

136
00:08:57.887 --> 00:08:59.569
I'm so sorry. Adam.

137
00:08:59.570 --> 00:09:01.569
What happened?

138
00:09:01.570 --> 00:09:03.293
He just...

139
00:09:03.294 --> 00:09:06.046
stopped breathing.

140
00:09:06.047 --> 00:09:09.362
Well. listen. you-you just...
you take whatever time you need.

141
00:09:09.363 --> 00:09:11.651
Don't worry about your
office hours. okay. Adam?

142
00:09:16.240 --> 00:09:17.030
What's wrong?

143
00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:19.095
I-I... I-I saw someone.

144
00:09:19.096 --> 00:09:20.714
It's okay. there's no one here.

145
00:09:20.715 --> 00:09:23.556
No one but me.

146
00:09:23.580 --> 00:09:25.046
Come here.

147
00:09:25.070 --> 00:09:26.436
It's okay.

148
00:09:26.460 --> 00:09:27.627
Shh...

149
00:09:27.628 --> 00:09:29.386
What right do you have to stop me right here?

150
00:09:29.387 --> 00:09:31.216
- I need to see that boy...
- J-Just get out of here.

151
00:09:31.217 --> 00:09:32.545
All right. all right. Get out of here.

152
00:09:32.546 --> 00:09:33.726
Cool. all right.

153
00:09:33.750 --> 00:09:38.036
Your towering respect for law is
just astounding as always. John.

154
00:09:38.037 --> 00:09:41.161
Oh. I see you managed to
steal from the cop as well.

155
00:09:41.162 --> 00:09:43.641
Eh. it's a campus cop. mate. big difference.

156
00:09:43.642 --> 00:09:45.519
Let's see. uh. victim collapsed.

157
00:09:45.520 --> 00:09:48.069
Witness found him with
blue lips and extremities.

158
00:09:48.070 --> 00:09:51.942
Says here that's consistent with
a sudden loss of circulation.

159
00:09:51.943 --> 00:09:53.142
So you know this bloke?

160
00:09:53.143 --> 00:09:55.467
He was friends with Adam.
my teaching assistant.

161
00:09:55.468 --> 00:09:57.415
All right. we'll need to talk to Adam.

162
00:09:57.416 --> 00:09:58.540
Okay. so does...

163
00:09:58.541 --> 00:10:01.260
that would be talking meaning talking. right?

164
00:10:01.261 --> 00:10:03.048
- Not harassing.
- Oh. yeah. well. you know me.

165
00:10:03.049 --> 00:10:05.429
I'm well-versed in the art of
pretending to be a gentleman.

166
00:10:05.430 --> 00:10:09.369
I do know you... that is
debatable. here we go.

167
00:10:13.050 --> 00:10:14.629
I know what I saw.

168
00:10:14.630 --> 00:10:16.671
He was there in the mirror.

169
00:10:16.672 --> 00:10:18.055
Did Adam see him?

170
00:10:18.056 --> 00:10:20.121
No. but he looked like the man you described

171
00:10:20.122 --> 00:10:22.580
in that house last night.

172
00:10:24.178 --> 00:10:26.949
There was no man. Lily.

173
00:10:26.950 --> 00:10:30.088
And there was no house.
either. it wasn't real.

174
00:10:30.089 --> 00:10:33.960
Wait. wait. last night you said
you saw something... we all did.

175
00:10:35.618 --> 00:10:38.121
We wanted to see something.

176
00:10:38.122 --> 00:10:39.453
It's called group hysteria.

177
00:10:39.454 --> 00:10:42.686
My cognitive psych professor
taught us about it.

178
00:10:42.687 --> 00:10:44.215
When you're trying to make sense

179
00:10:44.216 --> 00:10:47.603
out of things that just don't.

180
00:10:47.604 --> 00:10:50.413
I didn't come here to
talk about make-believe.

181
00:10:50.414 --> 00:10:52.996
I came here for Carter.

182
00:10:52.997 --> 00:10:55.456
I need to go clear my head.

183
00:10:55.480 --> 00:10:57.839
Lily. hi.

184
00:10:57.840 --> 00:10:59.043
You got a sec?

185
00:10:59.044 --> 00:11:01.076
Um. hi. Professor Simpson.

186
00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:04.121
Hey. have you seen Adam? I've
been trying to call him all day.

187
00:11:04.122 --> 00:11:05.810
Um. I left him in my dorm room.

188
00:11:05.811 --> 00:11:07.147
His phone's probably off.

189
00:11:07.148 --> 00:11:09.335
So. this. uh. chap Carter...

190
00:11:09.336 --> 00:11:11.053
he a mate of yours as well?

191
00:11:11.054 --> 00:11:15.231
Uh. it's okay. Lily. This is my. uh...

192
00:11:15.232 --> 00:11:17.866
colleague. of sorts. John Constantine.

193
00:11:17.890 --> 00:11:19.146
I'm just trying to piece together

194
00:11:19.170 --> 00:11:21.446
what happened to your mate last night.

195
00:11:21.470 --> 00:11:22.556
It's all right.

196
00:11:22.580 --> 00:11:23.916
You can answer his questions.

197
00:11:23.940 --> 00:11:25.346
I'm confident my associate

198
00:11:25.370 --> 00:11:27.606
is not gonna get you in trouble.

199
00:11:27.630 --> 00:11:29.686
We were at the cemetery.

200
00:11:29.710 --> 00:11:32.266
Look. we were just trying to have some fun.

201
00:11:32.290 --> 00:11:33.850
Any others with you?

202
00:11:34.197 --> 00:11:36.096
My friend Miranda.

203
00:11:36.120 --> 00:11:38.413
And Adam. I should get back to him.

204
00:11:38.414 --> 00:11:40.643
He felt terrible about missing office hours.

205
00:11:40.644 --> 00:11:42.996
He's been taking this project
of yours very seriously...

206
00:11:42.997 --> 00:11:44.991
That's fine. You just tell
him we'll pick back up

207
00:11:44.992 --> 00:11:46.093
when he's ready. all right?

208
00:11:46.094 --> 00:11:48.328
You take care and have a good night.

209
00:11:48.329 --> 00:11:49.378
Thank you.

210
00:11:53.025 --> 00:11:55.307
So. The cemetery. eh?

211
00:11:55.308 --> 00:11:57.384
- Got what you need. John?
- No. I don't.

212
00:11:57.385 --> 00:11:58.690
She's hiding something

213
00:11:58.691 --> 00:12:00.239
and so are you.

214
00:12:00.240 --> 00:12:01.788
But at least I know where to start.

215
00:12:28.536 --> 00:12:29.604
Hah.

216
00:12:30.051 --> 00:12:32.601
- Nice landing.
- How's your old friend?

217
00:12:32.602 --> 00:12:34.817
Not very friendly. to be honest with you.

218
00:12:34.818 --> 00:12:36.107
Maybe that's because you'd rather

219
00:12:36.108 --> 00:12:37.349
wallow in the dead friends

220
00:12:37.350 --> 00:12:39.119
than deal with them when they're alive.

221
00:12:39.120 --> 00:12:41.524
Uh. you're a bit late to the party. mate.

222
00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:43.660
Ritchie used to be my ace.

223
00:12:43.661 --> 00:12:45.537
True partner in crime.

224
00:12:45.538 --> 00:12:48.140
All the others were too
easily dazzled. you know?

225
00:12:48.141 --> 00:12:50.555
Used to worship the
bloody ground I walked on.

226
00:12:51.190 --> 00:12:52.751
Modesty.

227
00:12:52.752 --> 00:12:53.791
I thought to myself.

228
00:12:53.792 --> 00:12:56.003
here's someone with a sense of purpose.

229
00:12:56.004 --> 00:12:58.464
and twisted enough to face the darkest forces

230
00:12:58.465 --> 00:12:59.613
that evil has to offer.

231
00:13:04.376 --> 00:13:06.964
Sounds like an interesting
basis for a friendship.

232
00:13:08.950 --> 00:13:11.416
Ah. it's a requirement with me. mate.

233
00:13:12.574 --> 00:13:14.884
Newcastle left a mark on our crew.

234
00:13:15.392 --> 00:13:18.258
We all shut down in some
way. but Ritchie's fall...

235
00:13:19.792 --> 00:13:21.468
that was the greatest.

236
00:13:24.150 --> 00:13:26.587
He sounds like he could be useful to us.

237
00:13:26.611 --> 00:13:29.901
Maybe you can... guide him back into action.

238
00:13:32.936 --> 00:13:36.769
Oh. I'm not exactly a
guiding light. now. am I?

239
00:13:36.770 --> 00:13:38.770
Oh. bollocks.

240
00:13:39.590 --> 00:13:43.007
Really get on my nerves sometimes.

241
00:13:43.769 --> 00:13:45.007
All right.

242
00:13:51.091 --> 00:13:52.649
Fold és a levego.

243
00:13:54.249 --> 00:13:56.376
hogy igaz legyen reveal

244
00:13:56.842 --> 00:13:59.421
E-te-titok.

245
00:14:00.988 --> 00:14:04.367
♪ ♪

246
00:14:58.851 --> 00:14:59.857
Who's there?

247
00:14:59.858 --> 00:15:01.425
Open the door.

248
00:15:02.762 --> 00:15:04.144
You have to open the door. quick.

249
00:15:04.145 --> 00:15:05.184
before he comes back.

250
00:15:05.185 --> 00:15:07.185
What? Why? Why can't you do it?

251
00:15:22.320 --> 00:15:24.729
Beeswax candle. hieroglyphics
and residual ash.

252
00:15:24.730 --> 00:15:28.337
Now. you put those three together.
Ritchie. and what do you get?

253
00:15:28.338 --> 00:15:29.928
An Egyptian ritual.

254
00:15:31.275 --> 00:15:34.041
Well. I'm glad to see it's just
your courage that's wavering.

255
00:15:34.042 --> 00:15:35.754
Now. I found those things in the cemetery

256
00:15:35.755 --> 00:15:37.613
where your. uh. assistant

257
00:15:37.614 --> 00:15:39.086
was having a skinful last night.

258
00:15:39.087 --> 00:15:40.926
And by the looks of the
glyphs. I'd say it was a ritual

259
00:15:40.927 --> 00:15:42.686
for out-of-body travel.

260
00:15:42.687 --> 00:15:46.097
Now. where do you think that
a bunch of college students

261
00:15:46.098 --> 00:15:47.293
would get that balmy idea. eh?

262
00:15:47.294 --> 00:15:49.374
No. No. no. No. that's...

263
00:15:49.948 --> 00:15:50.800
Oh... It's gone.

264
00:15:50.800 --> 00:15:51.783
What's gone. Ritchie?

265
00:15:51.784 --> 00:15:53.020
It was. uh... it was a private journal.

266
00:15:53.021 --> 00:15:56.621
It was the private journal of Jacob Shaw.

267
00:15:57.087 --> 00:15:58.681
Jacob Shaw. I remember that name.

268
00:15:58.682 --> 00:16:00.187
He was the bloke who fancied himself

269
00:16:00.188 --> 00:16:01.834
a traveler to alternative realms. right?

270
00:16:01.835 --> 00:16:02.385
Right. right. right.

271
00:16:02.386 --> 00:16:04.239
The journal records his success

272
00:16:04.240 --> 00:16:06.963
with the Egyptian dream temple technique.

273
00:16:06.964 --> 00:16:07.905
but...

274
00:16:08.301 --> 00:16:09.848
Shaw stopped writing

275
00:16:09.849 --> 00:16:11.760
after he shot his protégé.

276
00:16:12.225 --> 00:16:13.928
Ooh. Well. you know. in my opinion.

277
00:16:13.929 --> 00:16:15.476
the best ones are always
a little bit cracked.

278
00:16:15.477 --> 00:16:17.269
And Shaw. he said it was a hunting accident.

279
00:16:17.270 --> 00:16:18.690
He was awaiting trial for murder

280
00:16:18.691 --> 00:16:20.357
when he fell into...

281
00:16:20.541 --> 00:16:21.430
Get this...

282
00:16:21.431 --> 00:16:22.889
A catatonic state.

283
00:16:23.440 --> 00:16:26.140
Catatonic. Like. uh. Carter.

284
00:16:26.141 --> 00:16:27.984
Yeah. Like Carter.

285
00:16:27.985 --> 00:16:30.370
And Shaw died a few weeks later. and...

286
00:16:32.400 --> 00:16:33.471
there was a theory.

287
00:16:33.472 --> 00:16:34.395
What theory?

288
00:16:34.396 --> 00:16:36.188
An "Elvis lives" kind of theory?

289
00:16:36.894 --> 00:16:38.883
They say Shaw's consciousness

290
00:16:38.884 --> 00:16:40.540
traveled to another dimension

291
00:16:40.541 --> 00:16:42.929
and stayed there to escape his fate.

292
00:16:42.930 --> 00:16:44.563
Well. that does make for a better story.

293
00:16:44.564 --> 00:16:47.871
One that... sparked the imagination

294
00:16:47.872 --> 00:16:51.603
- of your young teaching student.
- Yeah.

295
00:16:51.604 --> 00:16:53.600
Well. if Adam's tried it
once. he'll try it again.

296
00:16:54.410 --> 00:16:56.676
And it's up to us to beat him to it.

297
00:16:56.677 --> 00:16:58.164
- Us.
- It... But...

298
00:17:05.585 --> 00:17:06.738
Still not picking up.

299
00:17:07.750 --> 00:17:09.180
Miranda was really upset.

300
00:17:09.181 --> 00:17:10.654
I think we should go look for her.

301
00:17:10.847 --> 00:17:11.562
Hmm.

302
00:17:12.762 --> 00:17:13.562
What?

303
00:17:14.828 --> 00:17:16.174
I just have this...

304
00:17:16.988 --> 00:17:17.797
feeling.

305
00:17:18.941 --> 00:17:19.797
What feeling?

306
00:17:21.548 --> 00:17:23.138
What if Miranda's...

307
00:17:26.018 --> 00:17:27.189
back there?

308
00:17:27.190 --> 00:17:28.869
You mean at that house?

309
00:17:28.870 --> 00:17:29.835
If her consciousness

310
00:17:29.836 --> 00:17:31.124
- traveled back...
- No. Adam.

311
00:17:31.125 --> 00:17:33.120
If it did. if it did...

312
00:17:33.825 --> 00:17:35.501
then we have to back there and get her.

313
00:17:36.635 --> 00:17:37.664
You just want to go back there

314
00:17:37.665 --> 00:17:39.283
because it's exciting for you.

315
00:17:39.284 --> 00:17:40.907
No. 'Cause if Miranda's back there.

316
00:17:40.908 --> 00:17:42.320
it is my fault.

317
00:17:43.444 --> 00:17:44.564
I need to find her.

318
00:17:44.950 --> 00:17:47.594
You can try finding her your way

319
00:17:47.595 --> 00:17:48.814
and I'll try mine.

320
00:17:50.301 --> 00:17:51.223
Where you going?

321
00:17:51.534 --> 00:17:53.425
Miranda dances to clear her head.

322
00:17:53.745 --> 00:17:54.988
I'll be at the gym.

323
00:17:56.419 --> 00:17:58.648
If those kids actually
made it into another realm.

324
00:17:58.649 --> 00:18:00.831
then they've opened gates
that won't be easy to close.

325
00:18:00.832 --> 00:18:02.177
In current conditions.

326
00:18:02.178 --> 00:18:03.900
anyone can be pulled in through that gate.

327
00:18:03.901 --> 00:18:04.982
not just the four that
took part in the ritual.

328
00:18:04.983 --> 00:18:06.808
Yeah. well. it's worse than that. John.

329
00:18:06.809 --> 00:18:08.050
Uh. Shaw had a theory.

330
00:18:08.051 --> 00:18:10.050
If-if you're killed in another dimension.

331
00:18:10.051 --> 00:18:12.201
your body here suffers
the same form of death.

332
00:18:12.202 --> 00:18:14.037
Ah. That would explain Carter.

333
00:18:14.432 --> 00:18:16.399
How the bloody hell did Adam
know about Shaw's journal?

334
00:18:16.400 --> 00:18:18.201
Uh. well. we were using...

335
00:18:18.202 --> 00:18:20.201
we've been using Shaw's research. just...

336
00:18:20.202 --> 00:18:21.217
Ha. ha. ha. yeah.

337
00:18:21.218 --> 00:18:23.217
For your new pet project. I presume.

338
00:18:23.218 --> 00:18:26.516
And what. exactly. would that
Nobel Prize-worthy effort be. eh?

339
00:18:26.517 --> 00:18:28.036
I don't believe you would understand.

340
00:18:28.037 --> 00:18:29.401
No? Well. you know. for idiots. then.

341
00:18:29.402 --> 00:18:30.596
- Singularity.
- Singularity.

342
00:18:30.597 --> 00:18:32.281
Do you understand it? Didn't think so.

343
00:18:32.282 --> 00:18:34.356
Singularity's the idea that when

344
00:18:34.357 --> 00:18:36.135
humanity and technology merge.

345
00:18:36.136 --> 00:18:38.643
a person's consciousness can find immortality

346
00:18:38.644 --> 00:18:39.834
inside a computer network.

347
00:18:39.835 --> 00:18:41.834
Oh. it's like a bomb shelter for your brain.

348
00:18:41.835 --> 00:18:43.660
That would be the idiot version. yes.

349
00:18:43.661 --> 00:18:46.135
Well. you're practically living
in one now. aren't you. Ritchie?

350
00:18:46.136 --> 00:18:48.003
You've done a great job of
making your world really small.

351
00:18:48.004 --> 00:18:48.898
Hey. listen to me.

352
00:18:48.899 --> 00:18:51.753
You really think I stopped
data-mining by choice?

353
00:18:51.754 --> 00:18:54.253
No. no. no. I got tired of
crashing hard drives. man.

354
00:18:54.254 --> 00:18:57.180
Way too many paranormal uprisings

355
00:18:57.181 --> 00:18:58.756
to keep track of.

356
00:18:58.757 --> 00:19:02.149
The darkness is almost here. John.

357
00:19:02.150 --> 00:19:04.949
If we don't find Adam and
close that portal now.

358
00:19:04.950 --> 00:19:07.490
who knows how many more
are gonna fall through?

359
00:19:07.491 --> 00:19:08.894
And I just...

360
00:19:09.651 --> 00:19:11.472
can't have that on my hands. John.

361
00:19:14.371 --> 00:19:15.524
We'll find him.

362
00:19:16.423 --> 00:19:17.237
We'll find him.

363
00:19:22.522 --> 00:19:24.888
Doo-wat ak-em

364
00:19:24.889 --> 00:19:27.100
ka ren el-bee

365
00:19:27.101 --> 00:19:29.637
ak-em ma-at.

366
00:19:35.105 --> 00:19:37.374
Miranda. I knew you'd be here.

367
00:19:38.310 --> 00:19:39.327
What...?

368
00:19:40.903 --> 00:19:42.676
He's after me. We have to hide.

369
00:19:42.677 --> 00:19:44.855
Miranda. I am so sorry...

370
00:19:44.856 --> 00:19:47.760
Shh.

371
00:19:50.343 --> 00:19:51.689
Miranda?

372
00:20:16.691 --> 00:20:17.975
Looks like Alice has

373
00:20:17.976 --> 00:20:20.527
already slipped through the looking glass.

374
00:20:35.303 --> 00:20:37.133
- Jacob Shaw.
- That's right.

375
00:20:37.134 --> 00:20:39.622
- What do you want?
- Exactly this. young lady.

376
00:20:39.623 --> 00:20:40.578
Thank you for asking.

377
00:20:40.579 --> 00:20:43.190
No. no. please! Stop!

378
00:20:49.670 --> 00:20:50.555
Defensive wounds.

379
00:20:50.556 --> 00:20:52.413
We need to wake him up now.

380
00:20:52.414 --> 00:20:53.176
Wake up!

381
00:20:53.177 --> 00:20:54.323
Ah... no. no. no!

382
00:20:55.590 --> 00:20:56.639
Not now.

383
00:20:56.640 --> 00:20:57.600
Ah. I got you.

384
00:20:57.600 --> 00:20:58.456
Come on.

385
00:21:23.134 --> 00:21:25.040
It's Miranda.

386
00:21:25.472 --> 00:21:27.035
They found her...

387
00:21:27.929 --> 00:21:29.675
dead in the dance studio.

388
00:21:30.790 --> 00:21:32.861
They'll be shutting down the campus. next.

389
00:21:33.407 --> 00:21:34.479
This. right here.

390
00:21:34.480 --> 00:21:35.829
this is. this is all my fault.

391
00:21:35.830 --> 00:21:37.829
Oh. spare me. will you?

392
00:21:37.830 --> 00:21:39.406
You didn't make Adam do the ritual.

393
00:21:39.407 --> 00:21:42.436
Gary... he unleashed that hunger demon...

394
00:21:42.437 --> 00:21:43.697
You are not Gary.

395
00:21:43.698 --> 00:21:45.599
And I brought this into Adam's life.

396
00:21:45.600 --> 00:21:47.600
You see what we are. John?

397
00:21:49.299 --> 00:21:53.133
To other people. we are what you call cancer.

398
00:21:53.134 --> 00:21:55.735
And we're just spreading our disease.

399
00:21:57.138 --> 00:21:59.693
You know. when you're done
sitting on your bloody pity pot.

400
00:21:59.694 --> 00:22:01.694
we got work to do. all right?

401
00:22:03.289 --> 00:22:04.888
Pity pot. that's...

402
00:22:04.889 --> 00:22:06.211
that's good. John.

403
00:22:07.520 --> 00:22:10.290
Yeah. laugh it up. tell your jokes.

404
00:22:10.291 --> 00:22:11.872
but I'll tell you something.

405
00:22:13.374 --> 00:22:15.123
You don't fool me. man.

406
00:22:15.124 --> 00:22:16.794
Not anymore.

407
00:22:16.795 --> 00:22:18.192
I know your secret.

408
00:22:19.167 --> 00:22:22.333
I know what you pretend not to feel.

409
00:22:22.334 --> 00:22:23.703
You know why?

410
00:22:24.282 --> 00:22:25.551
'Cause...

411
00:22:25.552 --> 00:22:27.552
I'm feeling it right now.

412
00:22:34.357 --> 00:22:35.650
Let's go.

413
00:22:35.651 --> 00:22:39.717
There's still one life left
we might be able to save.

414
00:22:45.310 --> 00:22:46.432
Bollocks.

415
00:22:59.129 --> 00:23:01.109
Professor Simpson. thank
God. please. please come in.

416
00:23:01.110 --> 00:23:01.957
Where's Adam?

417
00:23:01.958 --> 00:23:04.041
I need to tell him about Miranda.

418
00:23:04.042 --> 00:23:05.030
Did you hear what happened?

419
00:23:05.031 --> 00:23:07.029
We just came from the gym.

420
00:23:07.030 --> 00:23:08.488
I-I found her body.

421
00:23:08.489 --> 00:23:10.761
There was so much blood.

422
00:23:10.762 --> 00:23:12.290
And I can't reach Adam.

423
00:23:12.291 --> 00:23:13.468
So...

424
00:23:15.971 --> 00:23:17.021
Lily.

425
00:23:17.929 --> 00:23:18.640
No.

426
00:23:18.974 --> 00:23:20.850
No. n-n-no. please no.

427
00:23:20.851 --> 00:23:24.008
We tried to save him. but he
was trapped in another world.

428
00:23:24.009 --> 00:23:27.015
No. I told him not to go back to that house.

429
00:23:30.348 --> 00:23:32.724
Wait... what house?

430
00:23:37.327 --> 00:23:38.643
I never saw him coming.

431
00:23:38.644 --> 00:23:41.735
I just felt the plastic
over my face. and I just...

432
00:23:41.736 --> 00:23:42.883
I just couldn't breathe.

433
00:23:49.044 --> 00:23:50.267
We died.

434
00:23:50.268 --> 00:23:52.268
so why are we still alive here?

435
00:23:55.035 --> 00:23:56.658
Is this hell?

436
00:23:58.724 --> 00:23:59.825
If we're still here.

437
00:24:00.743 --> 00:24:02.649
it's because Shaw wants us here.

438
00:24:13.336 --> 00:24:17.213
Allow me to apologize for not
giving you a proper welcome.

439
00:24:17.214 --> 00:24:20.808
It has been a very long time
since I've had any houseguests.

440
00:24:20.809 --> 00:24:23.543
And I've completely forgotten my manners.

441
00:24:24.291 --> 00:24:25.491
Forgive me.

442
00:24:28.291 --> 00:24:29.914
Polite.

443
00:24:29.915 --> 00:24:31.674
Respectful.

444
00:24:31.675 --> 00:24:33.867
You young people remind me of home.

445
00:24:33.868 --> 00:24:35.151
My old home.

446
00:24:35.152 --> 00:24:38.889
So... so restrictive.

447
00:24:40.522 --> 00:24:42.635
It's different in this house.

448
00:24:43.392 --> 00:24:45.110
And I've always been a sportsman.

449
00:24:45.727 --> 00:24:47.661
So that's what we do here.

450
00:24:48.381 --> 00:24:49.661
We play.

451
00:24:50.451 --> 00:24:52.729
Now. I'm going to choose a weapon.

452
00:24:53.228 --> 00:24:57.920
and you run along.

453
00:24:58.235 --> 00:24:59.471
You have free reign.

454
00:24:59.472 --> 00:25:02.389
just know that I will find you.

455
00:25:02.390 --> 00:25:04.276
Okay. come on.

456
00:25:04.277 --> 00:25:06.028
Come on. let's go.

457
00:25:12.202 --> 00:25:14.530
You control this place.

458
00:25:14.531 --> 00:25:16.474
Which means you built it.

459
00:25:16.475 --> 00:25:18.728
Hmm. you're smarter than your friends.

460
00:25:18.729 --> 00:25:22.997
Smart enough to know that this
is your reality and not mine.

461
00:25:24.018 --> 00:25:25.547
And that you can't hurt me here.

462
00:25:26.528 --> 00:25:28.987
Interesting hypothesis.

463
00:25:28.988 --> 00:25:31.377
Of course. there is only one true way

464
00:25:31.378 --> 00:25:33.755
for a hypothesis to become
a scientific theory.

465
00:25:35.322 --> 00:25:37.269
Do you know what that is?

466
00:25:37.270 --> 00:25:38.780
Of course.

467
00:25:38.781 --> 00:25:39.909
It means you got to test it. right?

468
00:25:39.910 --> 00:25:41.938
Test the hypothesis.

469
00:25:43.143 --> 00:25:44.800
That's exactly right.

470
00:25:49.567 --> 00:25:50.643
So...

471
00:25:50.644 --> 00:25:52.644
shall we?

472
00:25:58.023 --> 00:25:59.467
Where are we?

473
00:25:59.468 --> 00:26:03.510
Oh. think of it as a spiritual safe house.

474
00:26:04.348 --> 00:26:06.639
This place is amazing. John.

475
00:26:06.640 --> 00:26:08.850
Jasper did all right. didn't he?

476
00:26:08.851 --> 00:26:11.584
Now. based on what you told us.
Shaw's drawing your friends back

477
00:26:11.585 --> 00:26:14.742
into his realm through reflective surfaces.

478
00:26:14.743 --> 00:26:16.196
In Egyptian magic.

479
00:26:16.197 --> 00:26:18.944
mirrors are doorways to
other spiritual planes.

480
00:26:18.945 --> 00:26:21.359
But lucky enough. our
mate. he put protections

481
00:26:21.360 --> 00:26:24.502
on any and all reflective
surfaces in this house.

482
00:26:24.503 --> 00:26:26.624
I don't know what to make of any of this.

483
00:26:26.625 --> 00:26:28.351
but thank you.

484
00:26:28.352 --> 00:26:32.042
Ah. the best thing you can do
is take a seat and have a rest.

485
00:26:36.752 --> 00:26:38.111
What do you two want to drink?

486
00:26:38.112 --> 00:26:39.410
Whiskey would be great.

487
00:26:39.411 --> 00:26:40.446
Yes. please.

488
00:26:40.447 --> 00:26:42.451
And my kingdom to make mine a double.

489
00:26:43.609 --> 00:26:45.966
My mom was supposed to pick
me up from the train station.

490
00:26:45.967 --> 00:26:47.764
I'm just gonna give her a quick call.

491
00:26:49.680 --> 00:26:50.117
Uh. n-n-no.

492
00:26:50.118 --> 00:26:52.385
- No. don't look at the phone!
- Wait! Wait! Wait!

493
00:27:35.421 --> 00:27:36.329
Lily.

494
00:27:36.330 --> 00:27:37.942
Oh. my God. Adam!

495
00:27:37.943 --> 00:27:40.643
What are you doing here?
No. you can't stay here.

496
00:27:40.644 --> 00:27:42.064
You-you have to go back. it's not safe here.

497
00:27:42.065 --> 00:27:44.751
- It's Shaw. isn't it?
- Look. he's a lunatic.

498
00:27:44.752 --> 00:27:46.850
He hunts us. and then he
brings us right back to life.

499
00:27:46.851 --> 00:27:48.921
It is a game that just never ends.

500
00:27:48.922 --> 00:27:51.636
But you can still get out of here.

501
00:27:51.637 --> 00:27:54.729
As long as he doesn't get to you. okay?

502
00:27:54.730 --> 00:27:55.722
- Okay.
- All right?

503
00:27:55.722 --> 00:27:56.607
Okay.

504
00:28:01.774 --> 00:28:03.744
Her pulse is racing. John.

505
00:28:03.745 --> 00:28:05.490
Which means two things.

506
00:28:05.491 --> 00:28:08.188
She's alive and she's scared.

507
00:28:08.850 --> 00:28:10.074
We need to get to her.

508
00:28:10.075 --> 00:28:11.021
No. John.

509
00:28:11.022 --> 00:28:12.384
- Oh. no. No!
- Ritchie. Ritchie.

510
00:28:12.385 --> 00:28:13.951
Ritchie. listen to me... we're going.

511
00:28:13.952 --> 00:28:15.236
- All right? We are going.
- I...

512
00:28:15.237 --> 00:28:16.522
I can't do it without you.

513
00:28:17.557 --> 00:28:19.138
Can't do it without you. Ritchie.

514
00:28:20.207 --> 00:28:21.040
Okay.

515
00:28:21.840 --> 00:28:24.041
There's only one way Shaw could pull Lily

516
00:28:24.042 --> 00:28:26.267
back into another world
without a proper ritual.

517
00:28:26.268 --> 00:28:28.271
It's a creation of his own design. right?

518
00:28:28.272 --> 00:28:29.316
- He built it.
- Right.

519
00:28:29.317 --> 00:28:31.584
So we need... we need a plan. Uh. Lily...

520
00:28:31.585 --> 00:28:33.904
She said they all ended up in
different rooms of a house...

521
00:28:33.905 --> 00:28:37.001
: And we can't help her
if we get killed. John.

522
00:28:37.002 --> 00:28:38.116
before we can find her.

523
00:28:38.117 --> 00:28:40.526
All right. so the first
order of business is...

524
00:28:40.527 --> 00:28:42.687
We find each other on the other side.

525
00:28:42.898 --> 00:28:44.182
That way. we got a better chance.

526
00:28:44.183 --> 00:28:45.462
Right. but what about our bodies?

527
00:28:45.463 --> 00:28:48.121
John. you don't even want to
know the dimensional mayhem

528
00:28:48.122 --> 00:28:50.921
it would cause if anything
happened to our bodies here

529
00:28:50.922 --> 00:28:52.719
while we're on another plane. all right?

530
00:28:52.720 --> 00:28:55.260
Can we just discuss that a little bit?

531
00:28:55.261 --> 00:28:56.301
Just a little.

532
00:28:57.887 --> 00:29:00.464
You know. I think we'll be all right here.

533
00:29:00.465 --> 00:29:01.984
- Now. come on. let's get to it.
- John. John. John. John.

534
00:29:01.985 --> 00:29:02.894
You got to understand.

535
00:29:02.895 --> 00:29:05.617
We are flying blind into his domain.

536
00:29:05.618 --> 00:29:06.550
He controls it all.

537
00:29:06.551 --> 00:29:08.342
The only rule there

538
00:29:08.343 --> 00:29:11.589
is Shaw is god.

539
00:29:11.590 --> 00:29:13.806
And it wouldn't be the
first one I've dealt with.

540
00:29:13.807 --> 00:29:16.334
So. shall we?

541
00:29:32.301 --> 00:29:34.116
Just like back in the day. eh?

542
00:29:34.117 --> 00:29:36.696
Yeah. a little too much like it.

543
00:29:45.628 --> 00:29:48.944
Doo-wat ak-em ka ren el-bee shoit.

544
00:29:48.945 --> 00:29:51.636
Doo-wat ak-em ma-at.

545
00:29:51.637 --> 00:29:54.803
Doo-wat ak-em ka ren el-bee shoit.

546
00:29:54.804 --> 00:29:57.025
Doo-wat ak-em ma-at.

547
00:31:04.828 --> 00:31:05.289
Ritchie.

548
00:31:17.618 --> 00:31:19.236
That's the real bogeyman.

549
00:31:19.237 --> 00:31:20.197
Come on.

550
00:31:26.437 --> 00:31:28.432
We need to find Lily now.

551
00:31:33.920 --> 00:31:36.209
Of course. a dead end.

552
00:31:36.210 --> 00:31:38.635
A fitting choice for our mad architect.

553
00:31:40.056 --> 00:31:41.534
Uh. John. wait.

554
00:31:42.884 --> 00:31:43.942
I can do this.

555
00:31:43.943 --> 00:31:47.246
I studied the principles of other planes.

556
00:31:47.247 --> 00:31:49.048
I can do this. John.

557
00:31:49.049 --> 00:31:51.952
I can overwrite his world.

558
00:31:52.420 --> 00:31:53.040
I know it.

559
00:32:05.571 --> 00:32:06.988
You're bloody doing it. mate.

560
00:32:16.465 --> 00:32:17.449
Nifty.

561
00:32:18.254 --> 00:32:19.218
Very nifty.

562
00:32:41.449 --> 00:32:42.112
John.

563
00:33:01.901 --> 00:33:02.814
Please.

564
00:33:03.769 --> 00:33:04.611
Hide me.

565
00:33:05.727 --> 00:33:07.025
He's watching.

566
00:33:08.696 --> 00:33:10.102
Who are you?

567
00:33:10.103 --> 00:33:11.741
Where's Shaw?

568
00:33:24.578 --> 00:33:26.074
I'm Jacob Shaw.

569
00:33:26.075 --> 00:33:27.228
And who are you?

570
00:33:42.630 --> 00:33:45.250
So the legend's true.

571
00:33:45.251 --> 00:33:47.247
You did come here to escape.

572
00:33:48.348 --> 00:33:49.556
I came here to live.

573
00:33:49.557 --> 00:33:52.055
You're an arrogant. bloody sod. aren't you?

574
00:33:52.056 --> 00:33:54.050
You're here to mutilate and murder.

575
00:33:54.051 --> 00:33:56.502
Beings of my own creation.

576
00:33:56.503 --> 00:33:58.460
Those students you butchered.

577
00:33:58.461 --> 00:34:00.461
they didn't just leap
out of your imagination.

578
00:34:01.096 --> 00:34:02.229
They were flesh and blood.

579
00:34:02.230 --> 00:34:04.941
Yes. and they invaded my space.

580
00:34:05.534 --> 00:34:08.427
My world. my rules.

581
00:34:08.428 --> 00:34:09.807
It's a lesson you're about to learn.

582
00:34:10.611 --> 00:34:13.622
Boy. you are a waste. man.

583
00:34:13.623 --> 00:34:16.305
You're just a psychopath. hacking up...

584
00:34:27.308 --> 00:34:29.608
These wounds. Ritchie. they're
his reality. not yours.

585
00:34:29.609 --> 00:34:31.260
You're the greater mind here.

586
00:34:31.261 --> 00:34:32.813
You can beat this guy!

587
00:34:32.814 --> 00:34:33.783
Ritchie.

588
00:34:33.784 --> 00:34:35.830
In this place. you...

589
00:34:36.842 --> 00:34:37.971
you decide.

590
00:34:38.470 --> 00:34:39.195
Ritchie. look at me.

591
00:34:39.196 --> 00:34:40.596
Look at me.

592
00:34:40.597 --> 00:34:42.682
Ritchie. look at me. Look at me.

593
00:34:44.522 --> 00:34:47.490
I believe in you. old son.

594
00:34:47.491 --> 00:34:49.068
Now. bloody do it!

595
00:34:50.108 --> 00:34:50.903
Do it!

596
00:35:06.470 --> 00:35:09.774
Some god you turned out to be. Shaw.

597
00:35:11.002 --> 00:35:12.922
You forgot the sun.

598
00:35:13.440 --> 00:35:14.560
No...

599
00:35:19.797 --> 00:35:22.498
- No!
- Oh. yes.

600
00:35:23.736 --> 00:35:25.933
All this time you spent here.

601
00:35:25.934 --> 00:35:28.521
you could've been building worlds.

602
00:35:28.522 --> 00:35:30.526
You could've been redefining life

603
00:35:30.527 --> 00:35:32.154
and how we live it.

604
00:35:32.155 --> 00:35:34.861
The day you gave into your weakness. Shaw.

605
00:35:35.905 --> 00:35:39.015
that was the day you became obsolete.

606
00:35:39.016 --> 00:35:41.016
This is my world!

607
00:35:42.108 --> 00:35:43.369
Not anymore.

608
00:35:53.058 --> 00:35:54.516
We have to get out of here.

609
00:35:54.517 --> 00:35:55.816
This way. mate. Come on.

610
00:35:59.435 --> 00:36:00.449
Come on. Ritchie.

611
00:36:00.450 --> 00:36:01.275
Okay.

612
00:36:22.870 --> 00:36:24.422
Nice job. Ritchie.

613
00:36:24.423 --> 00:36:26.423
You even got the temperature right.

614
00:36:27.807 --> 00:36:28.847
Lily.

615
00:36:34.710 --> 00:36:35.806
What's happening?

616
00:36:35.807 --> 00:36:37.184
Shaw's world is collapsing.

617
00:36:37.185 --> 00:36:38.243
We need to get out of here right now.

618
00:36:38.244 --> 00:36:39.016
Let's go!

619
00:36:41.496 --> 00:36:43.115
What are you doing? We have to go!

620
00:36:44.672 --> 00:36:46.610
This is as far as we go.

621
00:36:46.611 --> 00:36:47.458
No.

622
00:36:47.459 --> 00:36:49.664
No! No! No!

623
00:36:49.665 --> 00:36:52.370
No! No! No!

624
00:36:52.371 --> 00:36:55.302
No! They're all still in
there! We have to do something!

625
00:36:55.303 --> 00:36:56.588
There's nothing we can do for them.

626
00:36:56.589 --> 00:36:57.966
No! Come on! It's too late!

627
00:37:09.543 --> 00:37:11.270
Nothing we could've done. Lily.

628
00:37:12.244 --> 00:37:14.315
They only existed inside that house.

629
00:37:14.931 --> 00:37:16.591
Shaw's gone forever.

630
00:37:16.592 --> 00:37:18.737
Their souls are free now.

631
00:37:18.738 --> 00:37:21.086
On to the next journey.

632
00:37:21.087 --> 00:37:21.557
Look at me.

633
00:37:56.370 --> 00:37:57.148
It's your turn.

634
00:37:57.149 --> 00:37:59.481
Oh... hold on a minute. squire.

635
00:37:59.482 --> 00:38:00.738
And if I go back.

636
00:38:02.018 --> 00:38:03.298
what happens to you?

637
00:38:07.063 --> 00:38:08.442
I stay here.

638
00:38:16.018 --> 00:38:19.133
Here happens to be an elaborate figment

639
00:38:19.134 --> 00:38:21.251
of your confused imagination.

640
00:38:22.781 --> 00:38:24.992
What was it you said to me in there?

641
00:38:25.896 --> 00:38:27.637
I decide what's real.

642
00:38:29.891 --> 00:38:30.611
This is it.

643
00:38:31.524 --> 00:38:34.197
John. this is the reality that I want.

644
00:38:35.397 --> 00:38:36.761
Simplicity.

645
00:38:36.762 --> 00:38:39.759
And endless possibility.

646
00:38:39.760 --> 00:38:42.159
This. John. this is. this is paradise.

647
00:38:42.160 --> 00:38:44.502
Oh. what makes you think that after a decade.

648
00:38:44.503 --> 00:38:47.171
you won't go off your trolley like Shaw?

649
00:38:47.807 --> 00:38:50.394
Shaw was mad to begin with.

650
00:38:50.395 --> 00:38:51.839
I'll do it right.

651
00:38:51.840 --> 00:38:53.839
I'll build a world here.

652
00:38:53.840 --> 00:38:57.048
I'll invent and create

653
00:38:57.049 --> 00:38:59.049
and thrive.

654
00:39:00.917 --> 00:39:03.749
You know what? I've already lost

655
00:39:03.750 --> 00:39:05.024
one good friend to this fight.

656
00:39:05.025 --> 00:39:07.297
And I'm not losing
another. so I'm calling you

657
00:39:07.298 --> 00:39:08.643
on your rubbish. Ritchie Simpson.

658
00:39:08.644 --> 00:39:10.018
If you stay here.

659
00:39:11.152 --> 00:39:12.352
you will go balmy.

660
00:39:13.760 --> 00:39:16.927
Balmier than you already are.
if that's at all possible.

661
00:39:19.581 --> 00:39:21.411
Better here than back home.

662
00:39:23.990 --> 00:39:24.989
At least.

663
00:39:24.990 --> 00:39:26.110
in this world. I can forget

664
00:39:27.327 --> 00:39:30.889
in this world. I can forget about
the darkness closing in on us. John.

665
00:39:33.355 --> 00:39:35.539
Look. I just don't.

666
00:39:35.540 --> 00:39:38.395
I don't want to be afraid anymore. John.

667
00:39:39.780 --> 00:39:40.588
Fine.

668
00:39:42.028 --> 00:39:42.752
That's fine.

669
00:39:43.642 --> 00:39:45.247
Indulge yourself. Ritchie.

670
00:39:46.225 --> 00:39:47.552
Just like Shaw.

671
00:39:48.315 --> 00:39:50.926
You're two visionary peas in a bloody pod.

672
00:39:50.927 --> 00:39:52.583
But do me a favor.

673
00:39:55.025 --> 00:39:56.583
Don't lie to yourself.

674
00:39:57.680 --> 00:40:00.447
This isn't about you creating something new.

675
00:40:01.887 --> 00:40:04.080
This is about you running away.

676
00:40:21.063 --> 00:40:22.577
Ritchie?

677
00:40:22.578 --> 00:40:25.410
Ritchie. Ritchie. Ritchie. Ritchie.

678
00:40:25.411 --> 00:40:27.319
Come on. come back to me.

679
00:40:27.320 --> 00:40:29.608
Come on. Ritchie. come on. man. come on.

680
00:40:29.609 --> 00:40:30.770
Come on. come back to me.

681
00:40:30.771 --> 00:40:32.715
Come back. Ritchie!

682
00:41:05.802 --> 00:41:07.651
Ah. you bugger.

683
00:41:48.367 --> 00:41:49.303
In our last class.

684
00:41:49.304 --> 00:41:53.109
we touched on the subject of Nirvana.

685
00:41:53.110 --> 00:41:55.110
Achieving enlightenment.

686
00:41:55.567 --> 00:41:57.919
In order to do that.

687
00:41:57.920 --> 00:42:00.037
certain truths must be accepted.

688
00:42:02.004 --> 00:42:03.425
First and foremost.

689
00:42:04.630 --> 00:42:06.800
suffering is unavoidable.

690
00:42:08.032 --> 00:42:09.264
Secondly.

691
00:42:09.265 --> 00:42:11.664
you must understand

692
00:42:11.665 --> 00:42:13.665
that suffering is caused by craving.

693
00:42:16.287 --> 00:42:20.135
Humankind desires relief in ways

694
00:42:20.136 --> 00:42:24.429
that ultimately do not satisfy the soul.

695
00:42:24.430 --> 00:42:26.930
The third and final truth

696
00:42:26.931 --> 00:42:28.413
is that inner peace

697
00:42:28.414 --> 00:42:30.573
is possible.

698
00:42:30.574 --> 00:42:34.577
But humankind's suffering won't end

699
00:42:34.578 --> 00:42:37.730
until we learn how to stop our desire.

700
00:42:37.731 --> 00:42:39.730
